# Getting started

> First page in this wiki. Replace me with something real.

This page exists so `keeba search` and `keeba bench` have something to find
on day zero. Once you start writing real pages, delete this one.

## What to write next

1. Open `entities/` and create one page per service / product / customer
   you care about. Use the [SCHEMA](../SCHEMA.md) as a template.
2. Open `concepts/` and document the architectural choices that aren't
   obvious from the code (why X over Y, what assumption Z relies on).
3. When something breaks, open `investigations/<YYYY-MM-DD>-<slug>.md`.
4. When you make a durable choice, open `decisions/<slug>.md`.

## The agent loop

| Time | What | Tool |
|---|---|---|
| As you work | Write pages by hand | editor + `keeba lint --staged` |
| Daily / weekly | Digest git + Slack into pages | the agent prompts in `agents/` |
| Every commit | Re-index for cheap agent reads | `keeba meta` (CI rebuilds it) |
| When you ask "what is X?" | BM25 over the wiki | `keeba search "X"` |
| When using Claude Code | Same query via MCP | `.mcp.json` is already wired |

